# Luxury Beauty Salon Website Walkthrough

I have completed the top page for the luxury beauty salon "LUMIÈRE".

## How to View
Since this is a static website, you can view it by simply opening the [index.html](file:///C:/Users/hangy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/luxury_salon/index.html) file in your browser.
**File Path**: [C:\Users\hangy\.gemini\antigravity\scratch\luxury_salon\index.html](file:///C:/Users/hangy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/luxury_salon/index.html)

## Features & Design Concept
-   **Japanese Luxury Aesthetic**:
    -   **Typography**: Used "Zen Old Mincho" for headings and vertical text to create a sophisticated, traditional yet modern atmosphere.
    -   **Colors**: A refined palette of Muted Gold (`#C5A059`) and Dark Charcoal (`#1A1A1A`) on a Cream (`#FAF9F6`) background.
    -   **Whitespace**: Generous spacing (padding/margin) to express luxury and calm.
-   **Technical Implementation**:
    -   **Responsive Design**: Fully compatible with mobile, tablet, and desktop screens.
    -   **Animations**: Subtle fade-in animations on scroll and a smooth parallax-like effect on the hero section.
    -   **Clean Code**: Built with semantic HTML5 and BEM-style CSS for maintainability.

## Important Note on Images
Due to current quota limits on image generation, I have used **CSS-styled placeholders** for the Hero, Concept, and Gallery images.
-   The placeholders have a subtle "shimmer" animation to mimic loading or a placeholder state.
-   You can replace these easily by adding images to the `images/` folder and uncommenting the `background-image` lines in [css/style.css](file:///C:/Users/hangy/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/luxury_salon/css/style.css) or adding `<img>` tags in HTML.

